      "text": "Kotlin Operators",
      "level": "h2"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "Operators are used to perform operations on variables and values.",
      "html": "<p>Operators are used to perform operations on variables and values.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "The value is called an operand, while the operation (to be performed between the two operands) is defined by an operator :",
      "html": "<p>The value is called an operand, while the operation (to be performed between the two operands) is defined by an <strong>operator</strong>:</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "In the example below, the numbers 100 and 50 are operands , and the + sign is an operator :",
      "html": "<p>In the example below, the numbers 100 and 50 are <strong>operands</strong>, and the\n<code>+</code> sign is an <strong>operator</strong>:</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "javascript",
        "tryItLink": "https://www.w3schools.com/kotlin/trykotlin.php?filename=demo_oper",
        "syntaxHighlighting": [],
        "classList": [
          "notranslate",
          "w3-white",
          "language-kotlin"
        ],
        "isNotranslate": true
      },
      "code": "var\nx\n=\n\n100\n\n+\n\n50",
      "language": "javascript",
      "code_html": "<pre class=\"notranslate w3-white language-kotlin\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-kotlin\"><span class=\"token keyword keyword-var\">var</span> x <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">100</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token number\">50</span></code></pre>",
      "code_classes": [
        "notranslate",
        "w3-white",
        "language-kotlin"
      ],
      "tryItLink": "https://www.w3schools.com/kotlin/trykotlin.php?filename=demo_oper",
      "syntax_highlighting_data": [],
      "class_list": [
        "notranslate",
        "w3-white",
        "language-kotlin"
      ],
      "is_notranslate": true
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "Although the + operator is often used to add together two values, like in the example above, it can also be used to add together a variable and a value, or a variable and a variable:",
      "html": "<p>Although the <code>+</code> operator is often used to add together two values, like in the example above, it can also be used to add together a variable and a value, or a variable and a variable:</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "javascript",
        "tryItLink": "https://www.w3schools.com/kotlin/trykotlin.php?filename=demo_oper2",
        "syntaxHighlighting": [],
        "classList": [
          "notranslate",
          "w3-white",
          "language-kotlin"
        ],
        "isNotranslate": true
      },
      "code": "var\nsum1\n=\n\n100\n\n+\n\n50\n\n// 150 (100 + 50)\n\n\nvar\nsum2\n=\nsum1\n+\n\n250\n\n// 400 (150 + 250)\n\n\nvar\nsum3\n=\nsum2\n+\nsum2\n// 800 (400 + 400)",
      "language": "javascript",
      "code_html": "<pre class=\"notranslate w3-white language-kotlin\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-kotlin\"><span class=\"token keyword keyword-var\">var</span> sum1 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">100</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token number\">50</span>       <span class=\"token comment\">// 150 (100 + 50)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword keyword-var\">var</span> sum2 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> sum1 <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token number\">250</span>     <span class=\"token comment\">// 400 (150 + 250)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword keyword-var\">var</span> sum3 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> sum2 <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> sum2    <span class=\"token comment\">// 800 (400 + 400)</span></code></pre>",
      "code_classes": [
        "notranslate",
        "w3-white",
        "language-kotlin"
      ],
      "tryItLink": "https://www.w3schools.com/kotlin/trykotlin.php?filename=demo_oper2",
      "syntax_highlighting_data": [],
      "class_list": [
        "notranslate",
        "w3-white",
        "language-kotlin"
